From d4cd9e1f0000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ETNA <etna@example.com>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Compute ribbon width with floor instead of round

Synthesised from upstream commit f289c1782e ("Compute ribbon width with
`floor` instead of `round` (#160)"). The hunk is rebased onto the
modern Prettyprinter.Internal module path; the historical patch was
against Data/Text/Prettyprint/Doc/Internal.hs. Reverse-applying this
patch reintroduces the bug where the ribbon width is rounded
(half-to-even) instead of floored, so half-fractional ribbon
fractions over-extend the ribbon by one column.

---
 prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs b/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs
index 0000000..0000000 100755
--- a/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs
+++ b/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs
@@ -1894,7 +1894,7 @@ remainingWidth lineLength ribbonFraction lineIndent currentColumn =
     columnsLeftInLine = lineLength - currentColumn
     columnsLeftInRibbon = lineIndent + ribbonWidth - currentColumn
     ribbonWidth =
-        (max 0 . min lineLength . round)
+        (max 0 . min lineLength . floor)
             (fromIntegral lineLength * ribbonFraction)

 -- $ Test to avoid surprising behaviour
